TITLE: Canada minister: Not safe yet for Syrian refugees to go home
SUMMARY: A Canadian minister has warned during a visit to Lebanon that Syria is not yet safe for millions of refugees to start going back home

TITLE: Canada minister: Not safe yet for Syrian refugees to go home
SUMMARY: A Canadian minister has warned during a visit to Lebanon that Syria is not yet safe for millions of refugees to start going back home

TITLE: WHO chief: Lack of help for Tigray crisis due to skin color
SUMMARY: The head of the World Health Organization has described the ongoing crisis in Ethiopia’s Tigray region as “the worst disaster on Earth” and asked if the reason global leaders haven't responded is due to “the color of the skin" of the people who live there

TITLE: Bombing at Kabul mosque kills 10, including prominent cleric
SUMMARY: An Afghan resident and police say that a bombing at a mosque in Kabul during evening prayers killed at least 10 people, including a prominent cleric, and wounded at least 27

TITLE: Syria denies it is holding American journalist Austin Tice
SUMMARY: Syria has denied it is holding U.S. journalist Austin Tice or other Americans.

TITLE: Venice fines tourist surfers for motoring down Grand Canal
SUMMARY: Venice authorities say two foreign tourists who sped down the city's Grand Canal on motorized boards have been heavily fined and the boards have been confiscated

TITLE: EU to host Serbia-Kosovo talks in Brussels amid tensions
SUMMARY: Wartime rivals Serbia and Kosovo will hold high-level crisis talks which the European Union mediators hope will de-escalate growing tensions in the Balkans

TITLE: Spain: 10 injured while leaving stopped train near wildfire
SUMMARY: Authorities in Spain say an approaching wildfire caused a train driver to stop and prepare to change directions, and several passengers were injured when they got off rather than wait

TITLE: Sweden presents plan to tackle high winter power bills
SUMMARY: Sweden’s government says it wants to pass legislation forcing the country’s public power transmission network operator to help reduce household and business electricity bills this winter

TITLE: First drought, now downpours as storms slam France, England
SUMMARY: France is being whipped by violent storms that have flooded Paris subway stations, snarled traffic and disrupted the president’s agenda

TITLE: Israel, Turkey to exchange ambassadors in diplomatic reset
SUMMARY: Israel and Turkey will restore full diplomatic relations and dispatch ambassadors for the first time in years, the latest step in months of reconciliation between the two countries

TITLE: Crimea 'sabotage' highlights Russia's woes in Ukraine war
SUMMARY: Fires and explosions has turned Russian-annexed Crimea into a flashpoint.

TITLE: Egypt's central bank governor resigns as economic woes mount
SUMMARY: Egypt’s central bank governor has resigned as the country has struggled to address its economic woes

TITLE: Kenya's president-elect will 'engage' in any court challenge
SUMMARY: Kenyan president-elect William Ruto says that if there’s a court challenge to the election results, “we will engage in those” as the country awaits a likely petition from losing candidate Raila Odinga

TITLE: Missing India soldier's body found on glacier after 38 years
SUMMARY: The remains of an Indian army soldier have been found more than 38 years after he went missing on a glacier at the highest point along the heavily militarized contested border between India and Pakistan in Kashmir

TITLE: Boat with 97 migrants aground on Greek island, no injuries
SUMMARY: Greek authorities say two sailboats carrying dozens of migrants have arrived on a southern Greek island early, with the first running aground on rocks

TITLE: Cargo ship breakdown blocks Rhine River traffic in Germany
SUMMARY: A cargo ship that broke down on the Rhine River caused a backup of other ships near the German town of St. Goar

TITLE: Bulgaria seizes 233 pounds of heroin worth $4.9 million
SUMMARY: Bulgarian authorities say customs have seized 106 kilograms (233 pounds) of heroin valued at 4.8 million euros ($4.9 million) found in a car entering from neighboring Turkey

TITLE: Bangladesh PM tells UN that Myanmar must take Rohingya back
SUMMARY: Bangladesh’s leader has told a visiting U.N. official that hundreds of thousands of ethnic minority Rohingya refugees living in camps in Bangladesh must return home to Myanmar, where they had fled violent persecution

TITLE: Afghanistan marks 1 year since Taliban seizure as woes mount
SUMMARY: The Taliban are marking a year since they seized the Afghan capital of Kabul

TITLE: Ethiopian rebels propose humanitarian truce amid drought
SUMMARY: An Ethiopian rebel group has proposed a humanitarian truce to facilitate assistance to hungry people in the country’s Oromia region as it warns of famine

TITLE: El Salvador extends state of exception; 50,000 arrested
SUMMARY: Some 50,000 people have been locked up in El Salvador since late March for alleged gang ties and the country's congress has now approved another month-long extension of the state of exception that suspends some rights in the name of combatting gangs

TITLE: Iraqi PM calls meeting of senior politicians to end crisis
SUMMARY: Iraq’s caretaker prime minister has held a meeting of senior political leaders and party representatives in an effort to end a monthslong crisis amid a power struggle between rival Shiite blocs

TITLE: Norway booting 30 royal guard members for illegal drug use
SUMMARY: Norway's military says 30 members of the country's prestigious royal guards unit will be booted out for using illegal drugs while on leave

TITLE: German leader condemns Abbas' '50 Holocausts' remark
SUMMARY: Germany’s chancellor says that he was “disgusted by the outrageous remarks” made by Palestinian President Mahmoud Abbas in Berlin, accusing Israel of committing “50 Holocausts” against Palestinians over the years
